ARTICLE.TITLE: Kate featured on British mag cover after 'most colorful trip' to Pakistan
ARTICLE.TEXT:
A widely circulated UK celebrity and royal news magazine has dedicated its latest cover to the Royal Couple's recent visit to Pakistan.

Adorned with a picture of Kate Middleton donning a dopatta, the magazine cover had green colour with a title that read: “Duchess Wins Hearts”.

The cover had another picture of the Duchess of Cambridge Kate Middleton and Duke of Cambridge Prince William wearing traditional headgear from northern Pakistan.

Cover of Hello Magazine. Photo: Twitter

The title of the second picture that reads “William and Kate’s Triumph” is bold and overlaps the content image.

The royal couple that recently completed their five-day visit to Pakistan held meetings with President Arif Alvi and Prime Minister Imran Khan.

The royal couple also met people from tinsel town, sports, and civil society during their stay in Islamabad.

The also undertook a visit to the northern areas of Pakistan where they witnessed effects of climate change and a melting glacier.

The couple then traveled to the eastern city of Lahore where they visited the iconic Badshahi Masjid and Shaukat Khanam Cancer Hospital.
